Title: Universality of random matrices in the microscopic limit and the Dirac
  operator spectrum
Authors: G. Akemann, P. H. Damgaard, U. Magnea, S. Nishigaki
Comments: 18 pages, LaTeX. One reference added
Report-no: ITP-UH-16/96, NBI-HE-96-43, NORDITA-96/59
Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B487 (1997) 721-738
\\
  We prove the universality of correlation functions of chiral unitary and
unitary ensembles of random matrices in the microscopic limit. The essence of
the proof consists in reducing the three-term recursion relation for the
relevant orthogonal polynomials into a Bessel equation governing the local
asymptotics around the origin. The possible physical interpretation as the
universality of soft spectrum of the Dirac operator is briefly discussed.
